		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />You need to stop listening to the homeless bums who don't know anything  <img src="./images/smilies/icon_smile.gif" alt=":)" title="Smile" />
<br />
<br />Nintendo had a few years of experience in the USA with arcades, Atari/Coleco/Intv games, and Game and Watch system.  That experience is exactly why they (not someone they hired) designed the NES to be more like  a VCR (front loading, ZIF) instead of an Atari (top loading).  All the empty space is there on purpose to make the device more impressive.  They also specifically did not call it a video game system, since that was a bad time for the industry.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
